parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS master brake cylinder can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: vehicle pulls to one side when brakes are applied
vehicle slides or crashes when brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window system can cause inconvenience and discomfort for the driver and passengers, and in some cases, obstruct visibility.
symptoms: The driver-side power window is inoperative
the window does not roll up or down
the window is stuck in an open or closed position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the rear window defroster can reduce visibility, especially in cold or snowy weather, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The center wire of the rear window defroster is malfunctioning
the rear window defroster is not working
the rear window is foggy or icy.
